replies.body:
I used to main support, and the reason I stopped was not because of crappy adc's, people not helping me ward, and not getting credit for things, it's because Riot does everything is can to FORCE you onto either a tanky melee or a squishy healer. If Rito really wanted to open this game up, they would make APC viable as support. Since they have all but removed them from mid lane with the exception of maybe a Fizz, Lux or occasional cho, they really could easily shift the AP to bot lane, and it would be fun as hell. 



{{champion:161}} {{champion:1}} {{champion:34}} {{champion:106}} {{champion:48}} {{champion:69}} 

All of these supports can hard carry a game. 

Stop playing the same boring stuff that you see on every stream, there are STILL champions out there that shine in "off-meta" roles, until Riot nerfs them of course. Vel'Koz deals TONS of damage, I mean TONS. I regularly out damage everyone in the game on both teams as Vel support. He has great CC and ridiculous damage. Voli support in plat and down is simply broken. Trundle, while he may suck in lane until like lvl 6-9 once you break out of lanning pahse you are suddenly a god even if you are 0-5-2. Anivia is great if your ADC sucks or people keep leaving a lane open and you can suck up some CS. She is even better with a good vayne as you can double stun, plus her lvl 1 is incredibly strong, not to mention her tower baiting ability. 

